does how often you check for email have an impact on the system response time stanford answers stanford university stanford answers does how often you check for email have an impact on the system response time categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home does how often you check for email have an impact on the system response time search this site stanford's logs show that some email clients check for mail as often as once per minute which translates to 1440 times per day the email servers already process millions of connections each day so if many people check mail this frequently it slows the delivery of everyone's email particularly during peak hours when the system is heavily loaded please check the settings or options of your email program to see how often it is configured to check for mail for automated checking it services recommends an interval of 15 minutes of course you can check for mail manually at any time especially if you are expecting an important email stanford email stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
